WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.960
In the last video you saw Emil make some tweaks to the styling of this website.

00:00:07.960 --> 00:00:12.500
Now we're going to kind of go back to what we were talking about prior to that, navigation.

00:00:12.500 --> 00:00:17.280
And I'm going to show you a different way to add navigation to a Quarto website,

00:00:17.280 --> 00:00:22.379
and that's this thing called a listing. So a really common use of a listing,

00:00:22.379 --> 00:00:26.160
and this is where you might have seen it used before, is in a blog. The page that

00:00:26.160 --> 00:00:29.680
makes that listing of all the blog posts that people sort of land on and then can

00:00:29.760 --> 00:00:35.040
browse through, that's an example of a listing. So we're going to add one of those to this website,

00:00:35.040 --> 00:00:38.160
and then I'm going to talk about a few of the other features of listings that make it a really

00:00:38.160 --> 00:00:43.119
good candidate for adding other things to your website, like a list of projects, or a list of

00:00:43.119 --> 00:00:49.040
talks, or a list of publications. Okay, so I'm going to head back over to rstudio. Here's our

00:00:49.040 --> 00:00:54.560
website project as we left it. And one thing you'll notice is there's actually already some

