going to turn off. Okay, so just re-rendering just to show you I've got rid of those. The other thing

00:10:31.200 --> 00:10:34.960
that I think, when you have a table, like these little images don't really add much, so you might

00:10:34.960 --> 00:10:41.280
want to get rid of them. Or you might have additional things you've specified in that yaml

00:10:41.280 --> 00:10:47.280
that you want to include that wouldn't be included by default. So I'm going to add this yaml. This

00:10:47.280 --> 00:10:55.679
yaml option is called fields. What do you want to show up in the listing as the columns in this

00:10:55.679 --> 00:11:05.039
table case? So what fields do I want? I want title, and I want the description, and I want categories.

00:11:07.280 --> 00:11:11.280
I don't think I want the date, right? Projects aren't really often associated with a specific

