I might change categories to skills. So let's make that change, and then I'll bring that up

00:11:46.479 --> 00:11:51.119
a bit bigger again, right? Now this feels more like a project portfolio, because I've got what's

00:11:51.119 --> 00:11:57.440
the project name, what did I do, and what were the skills I demonstrated in doing it. So that's a

00:11:57.440 --> 00:12:02.320
really simple kind of way you can customize these listings. Use that type table, and then you can

00:12:02.320 --> 00:12:08.080
play with what shows up in the columns, and what the column names are. But listings are incredibly

00:12:08.080 --> 00:12:12.960
customizable. So the first thing I want to do is show you an example of someone using listings,

00:12:12.960 --> 00:12:17.840
which really demonstrates the breadth of things you can do. So here's an example of someone using

00:12:17.840 --> 00:12:22.640
a listing. This is Andrew Heiss's teaching web page, and I want to show you some of the things

00:12:22.640 --> 00:12:27.520
that go beyond what I've shown you so far with listings. So the first thing is that you can have

00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:34.400
more than one listing on a page. So in this case, Andrew's using a listing for each academic year.

00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:38.880
So there's a listing that's generating these first two items, and there's a separate listing

00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:42.640
that's generating these next three. So the first thing to know is you can have more than one listing

00:12:42.640 --> 00:12:48.880
on a page. And along with that, you can put a listing wherever you want on the page. So if you

00:12:48.880 --> 00:12:53.840
want some content first, and then to have the listing, you can do that. And the way Andrew's

00:12:53.840 --> 00:12:59.440
using that here is just to say, in his source, he's got like, here is where the listing goes for this

00:12:59.440 --> 00:13:05.520
year. Here is where the listing goes for last year. And then the other thing that's going on

00:13:05.520 --> 00:13:12.559
here is he is not using that type table grid or default like we've seen so far. He has built a

00:13:12.559 --> 00:13:18.880
completely custom template for how each of the items appears. So in his custom template, there's

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:24.960
a place to put the sort of hex sticker. He's controlling the way that the title appears,

00:13:24.960 --> 00:13:30.400
that there's in this case like a course number and where it was taught, and then these really

00:13:30.400 --> 00:13:34.799
nice little orange links. These are kind of a custom part of his template. Sometimes there's

00:13:34.799 --> 00:13:39.919
only one, sometimes there's a couple. So listings are really powerful in the way that you can

00:13:39.919 --> 00:13:45.840
customize them as well. Okay, so that's listings. This really powerful way to add pages where you're

00:13:45.840 --> 00:13:51.359
just listing other content in a Koto website. So one thing I wanted to mention as we wrap up is

00:13:51.359 --> 00:13:56.880
that if you've got your page now built out, but you're like, I don't need a blog, I don't need

